Literally the worst papa johns we have ever tried to order from. I know, I know - a Chicago sports blog ordering pizza from papa johns should be outlawed, but we had just got off the boat and were starving. We thought "Deep dish is going to take too long, let's just get papa johns because it will be quick" We were WAY off. After waiting two hours we tried tracking my pizza - that was broken. Then we tried calling. A clown answered and then told us our pizza was on the way. 30 minutes later, I called back. Another idiot picked up. He said it was out for delivery and should be there by the time we got off the phone. At this point, we were dying of starvation, so when another 30 minutes passed, we were about to go to this papa johns and make the pizza ourselves. But, we were so weak from starvation we decided to call again. The manager finally got on the phone and said the pizza was STILL THERE!!! He apologized, told us this was refund but that he would "make sure" the driver right next to him would bring us our pizza. I accepted his apology and gesture. Stuff happens you know? When another hour passed, we felt a fury that hasn't been felt in years. We called again and the manager said he couldn't get in touch with his own driver. I repeat...the manager doesn't know how to get a hold of his employees. We told him to forget it and we would make our own food - 3.5 hours later. He insisted they were making our order again and sending it. SO, while in the bathroom, we got a call that the pizza was downstairs. When we saw the call we went down to the lobby - I tracked the time - it was 3 to 4 minutes since they had called. I got to the lobby and the driver had already left. AND THEY TOOK OUR PIZZAS WITH THEM!! I called the manager back and he said it was policy not to leave food with the doorman, when I explained that this was unacceptable. He hung up the phone. This not only was terrible customer service - we were literally weak from starvation. CALLING ALL PEOPLE OF CHICAGO - NEVER ORDER PIZZA HERE!
